	</div><p>Source : cette figure est extraite de Beintema et Elliott (2009). Elle provient d’un ensemble de données ASTI et de sources secondaires qui sous-tendent Beintema et Stads (2008ab) et Stads et Beintema (2009).</p><p>-</p><p>-</p><p>-</p><a name="eztoc348771_1_7" id="eztoc348771_1_7"></a><h3><b>Références</b></h3><p>
Alston, J.M. 2010. Science of Science Policy: Evidence and Lessons from Studies of Agricultural R&amp;D. Contribution au Workshop on Science of Science Measurement. National Science Foundation, Washington D.C., États-Unis, 2-3 décembre 2010.<br/> <a href="http://www.nsf.gov/sbe/sosp/econ/alston.pdf" target="_self">http://www.nsf.gov/sbe/sosp/econ/alston.pdf</a></p><p>Alston, J.M., Chan-Kang, C., Marra, M.C., Pardey, P.G. et Wyatt, T.J. 2000. A Meta Analysis of Rates of Return to Agricultural R&amp;D: <i>Ex Pede Herculem</i>? IFPRI Research Report No 113. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/pubs/abstract/113/rr113.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/pubs/abstract/113/rr113.pdf</a></p><p>Alston, J.M., Pardey, P.G. et Piggott, R.R. 2006. Synthesis of Themes and Policy Issues. Dans : Alston, J.M., Pardey, P.G. et Piggott, R.R. (Eds). <i>Agricultural R&amp;D in the Developing World: Too Little, Too Late?</i> International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis, p. 361-372. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/oc51.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/oc51.pdf</a></p><p>Alston, J.M., Andersen, M.A., James, J.S. et Pardey, P.G. 2010. <i>Persistence Pays: U.S. Agricultural Productivity Growth and the Benefits from Public R&amp;D Spending</i>. Springer, New York, États-Unis.</p><p>
Banque mondiale. 2007. Rapport sur le développement dans le monde 2008 : L’agriculture au service du développement. Banque mondiale, Washington, D.C., États-Unis.<br/><b> </b><a href="http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTRDM2008INFRE/Resources/French-version-WDR-2008-July-7.pdf" target="_self">http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTRDM2008INFRE/Resources/French-version-WDR-2008-July-7.pdf</a></p><p>Beintema, N. et Elliott, H. 2009. Setting meaningful investment targets in agricultural research and development: challenges, opportunities and fiscal realities. Réunion d'experts sur Comment nourrir le monde en 2050, Organisation des Nations unies pour l'alimentation et l'agriculture, Rome, Italie, 24-26 juin. <a href="ftp://ftp.fao.org/docrep/fao/012/ak978e/ak978e00.pdf" target="_self">ftp://ftp.fao.org/docrep/fao/012/ak978e/ak978e00.pdf</a></p><p>Beintema, N.M. et Stads, G.J. 2006. Agricultural R&amp;D in Sub-Saharan Africa: An Era of Stagnation. ASTI Background Report. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/AfricaRpt_200608.pdf" target="_self">http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/AfricaRpt_200608.pdf</a></p><p>Beintema, N.M. et Stads, G.J. 2008a. <i>Measuring Agricultural Research Investments: A Revised Global Picture</i>. ASTI Background Note. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/global_revision.pdf" target="_self">http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/Global_revision.pdf</a></p><p>Beintema, N.M. et Stads, G.J. 2008b. <i>Diversity in Agricultural Research Resources in the Asia-Pacific Region. </i>Synthesis. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis ; Asia-Pacific Association of Agricultural Research Institutions, Bangkok, Thaïlande. <a href="http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/APC_synthesis.pdf" target="_self">http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/APC_synthesis.pdf</a></p><p>Beintema, N.M. et Stads, G.J. 2010. Public Agricultural R&amp;D Investments and Capacities in Developing Countries. Recent Evidence for 2000 and Beyond. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/GCARD-BackgroundNote.pdf" target="_self">http://www.asti.cgiar.org/pdf/GCARD-BackgroundNote.pdf</a> </p><p>Beintema, N.M. et Stads, G.J. 2011. African Agricultural R&amp;D in the New Millennium: Progress for Some, Challenges for Many. IFPRI Food Policy Research Report. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/pr24.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/pr24.pdf</a> </p><p>Bindraban, P.S. et Rabbinge, R. 2004. Technologies That Can Make A Difference: Enhancing Agricultural Productivity in Africa. IAC (InterAcademy Council), Amsterdam, Pays-Bas.</p><p>Dorward, A., Kydd, J., Morrison, J. et Urey, I. 2004. A policy agenda for pro-poor agricultural growth. <i>World Development, </i>32 : 73-89.</p><p>Echeverría, R.G. et Beintema, N.M. 2009. Mobilizing financial resources for agricultural research in developing countries: Trends and mechanisms. Global Forum for Agricultural Research, Rome, Italie. <a href="http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/261898/mobilizing%20financial%20resources%20for%20AR4D.pdf" target="_self">http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/261898/mobilizing financial resources for AR4D.pdf</a> </p><p>Evenson, R.E. 2001. Economic impacts of agricultural research and extension. Dans : Gardner, B.L. et Rausser, G.C. (Eds). <i>Handbook of Agricultural Economics</i>, <i>volume 1A : Agricultural Production</i>. Elsevier, New York, États-Unis, p. 573-628. </p><p>IAC. 2004. Realizing the Promise and Potential of African Agriculture: Science and Technology Strategies for Improving Agricultural Productivity and Food Security in Africa. IAC (InterAcademy Council), Amsterdam, Pays-Bas. <a href="http://www.interacademycouncil.net/?id=9989" target="_self">http://www.interacademycouncil.net/?id=9989</a> </p><p>Kerr, J. et Kolavalli, S. 1999. Impact of Agricultural Research on Poverty Alleviation: Conceptual Framework with Illustrations from the Literature. EPTD Discussion Paper No. 56. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://impact.cgiar.org/sites/default/files/KerrKolavalli1999.pdf" target="_self">http://impact.cgiar.org/sites/default/files/KerrKolavalli1999.pdf</a> </p><p>Maredia, M.K. et Raitzer, D.A. 2006. CGIAR and NARS partner research in sub-Saharan Africa: evidence of impact to date. Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research Science Council, Rome, Italie. <a href="http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/258389/CGIAR_WP_AI-proof3.pdf" target="_self">http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/258389/CGIAR_WP_AI-proof3.pdf</a> </p><p>Naseem, A., Omamo, S.W. et Spielman, D.J. 2006. The Private Sector in Agricultural R&amp;D: Policies and Institutions to Foster its Growth in Developing Countries. ISNAR Discussion Paper 6. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/isnardp06.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/isnardp06.pdf</a> </p><p>NEPAD. 2006. Le plan d’action consolidé de l’Afrique dans le domaine de la science et la technologie. NEPAD (Nouveau partenariat pour le développement de l'Afrique), Pretoria, République d’Afrique du Sud. <a href="http://www.nepadst.org/doclibrary/pdfs/ast_cpa_2007_fr.pdf" target="_self">http://www.nepadst.org/doclibrary/pdfs/ast_cpa_2007_fr.pdf</a> </p><p>Nkamleu, G.B., Gokowski, J. et Kazianga, H. 2003. Explaining the failure of agricultural production in Sub-Saharan Africa. Contribution à la 25th International Conference of Agricultural Economists, 16-22 août 2003, Durban, République d’Afrique du Sud. <a href="http://purl.umn.edu/25872" target="_self">http://purl.umn.edu/25872</a></p><p>Pardey, P.G. 2010. Reassessing Public–Private Roles in Agricultural R&amp;D for Economic Development. Dans : World Food Security: Can Private Sector R&amp;D Feed The Poor? The Crawford Fund Fifteenth Annual International Conference, Parliament House, Canberra 27–28 octobre 2009. Crawford Fund, Deakin, Australie, p. 13-23.<a href="http://www.instepp.umn.edu/documents/Pardey--Reassessing%20public-private%20roles%20in%20agricultural%20R&amp;D%20for%20economic%20development.pdf" target="_self">http://www.instepp.umn.edu/documents/Pardey--Reassessing public-private roles in agricultural R&amp;D for economic development.pdf </a></p><p>Pardey, P.G., Beintema, N.M., Dehmer, S. et Wood, S. 2006. Agricultural research: A growing global divide? IFPRI Food Policy Report. International Food Policy Research Institute, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/pr17.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/pr17.pdf </a></p><p>Roseboom, J., Cremers, M. et Lauckner, B. 2001. Agricultural R&amp;D in the Caribbean: An Institutional and Statistical Profile. ISNAR Research Report 19. International Service for National Agricultural Research, La Haye, Pays-Bas. <a href="http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/isnararchive/publicat/pdf/rr-19.pdf" target="_self">http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/isnararchive/publicat/pdf/rr-19.pdf</a> </p><p>Stads, G.J. et Beintema, N.M. 2009. <i>Public Agricultural Research in Latin America and the Caribbean: Investment and Capacity Trends</i>. ASTI Synthesis Report. International Food Policy Research Institute and Inter-American Development Bank, Washington, D.C., États-Unis. <a href="http://idbdocs.iadb.org/wsdocs/getdocument.aspx?docnum=35555685" target="_self">http://idbdocs.iadb.org/wsdocs/getdocument.aspx?docnum=35555685</a> </p><p>Thirtle, C., Lin, L. et Piess, J. 2003. The impact of research-led agricultural productivity growth on poverty reduction in Africa, Asia and Latin America. <i>World Development,</i> 31 : 1959-1975. </p><p>Union africaine. 2003. Déclaration sur l’agriculture et la sécurité alimentaire en Afrique. Union africaine, Assembly/AU/Decl.7(II), Maputo, Mozambique.<a href="http://bibliotecavirtual.clacso.org.ar/ar/libros/iss/pdf_fr/oau/HoSMaputo03declfr.pdf" target="_self">http://bibliotecavirtual.clacso.org.ar/ar/libros/iss/pdf_fr /oau/HoSMaputo03declfr.pdf</a></p><p>Wiggins, S. 2000. Interpreting changes from the 1970s to the 1990s in African agriculture through village studies. <i>World Development, </i>28 : 631-662.</p><p><a href="#_ftnref1" target="_self">[1]</a> Joshua Ariga est économiste auprès du Centre international de développement des engrais (IFDC), PO Box 2040, Muscle Shoals, Alabama, 35662, USA. Tél. : +1 (256) 381 6600 - E-mail : <a href="mailto:jariga@ifdc.org" target="_self">jariga@ifdc.org</a> - Web : <a href="http://www.ifdc.org/" target="_self">www.ifdc.org</a> </p><p><a href="#_ftnref2" target="_self">[2]</a> Les ETP sont calculés sur le temps réel que les chercheurs consacrent aux activités de R&amp;D. Par exemple, le corps professoral des universités mène des activités non liées à la R&amp;D dans le cadre de son travail et les ETP ne prennent en compte que les périodes consacrées exclusivement à la R&amp;D. </p><p><a href="#_ftnref3" target="_self">[3]</a> Les institutions comme l’AGRA sont financées par des fondations privées telles que la Fondation Bill &amp; Melinda Gates, la Fondation Ford et la Fondation Rockefeller ; ces institutions ont récemment augmenté le montant du financement qu’elles accordent à la recherche.</p>
		</div>
		
